# Tooltips

Every icon-only / non-self-explanatory control in the builder must have a
hover-hint. Use the JS-positioned `Tooltip` from `packages/builder/src/Tooltip.tsx`
— **never** the browser's native `title` attribute.

Why:

- Native tooltips show after a long delay, can't be styled, are inconsistent
  across OSes, and disappear when the cursor moves.
- The custom `Tooltip` is `position: fixed`, so it escapes the scrolling
  Options/Timeline columns' `overflow:auto` clip.
- It anchors above the trigger and survives keyboard focus (`onFocus`/`onBlur`).

## Rules

1. Wrap the trigger element with `<Tooltip text="…">…</Tooltip>` instead of
   passing `title="…"`. Use `Tooltip` for icon buttons, drag grips, segmented
   buttons that need extra context, anything where the rendered content alone
   doesn't communicate the action.
2. For inline help next to a form label, use `<InfoTip text="…" />` (the ⓘ
   button), or pass `hint="…"` to a `Field` if SSR safety matters more than
   clip-escape.
3. Keep `aria-label` on icon-only triggers — the tooltip is a visual
   augmentation, not a replacement for an accessible name.
4. Don't use the native `title` attribute. CI / lint shouldn't grep up new
   `title="..."` usages in this directory.

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<Tooltip text="Restart from the start and play">
  <IconButton aria-label="Restart" onClick={restart}>
    ↻
  </IconButton>
</Tooltip>

// ❌ BAD — native title; styled inconsistently and gets clipped on slow hover.
<IconButton aria-label="Restart" title="Restart" onClick={restart}>
  ↻
</IconButton>

// ✅ GOOD — inline help on a form label.
<Field label={<L tip="Random seed for jitter/humanize.">Seed</L>}>
  <Input … />
</Field>
```
